Developed a cross-platform chatting application leveraging Java and Python with networking concepts to enable real-time communication between users. Utilized Java for the client-side application and Python for the server-side implementation. Implemented socket programming to establish communication channels between clients and the server over a network. Employed multithreading to handle concurrent connections and ensure seamless communication. Integrated graphical user interfaces (GUIs) using JavaFX for the client application to enhance user experience and facilitate intuitive interaction. Implemented features such as text messaging, file sharing, and user authentication to enhance application functionality. Employed encryption and authentication mechanisms to ensure data security and privacy. Contributed to fostering seamless communication and collaboration among users across diverse platforms through a robust and reliable chatting application.
